---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Contact', url: '/contact/' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Contact WrenchStack — corrections, partnerships, press"
  description="Get in touch with WrenchStack. Corrections to product data, vendor partnership inquiries, press requests, or general feedback — all handled by a real human."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-orange-600">Contact</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-5xl">
        Get in touch
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
        Every email lands in a real human's inbox — usually answered within 48 hours.
        Pick the right address below so we route you to the right thing fastest.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-6">

      <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-orange-200 bg-orange-50 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">General inquiries</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Feedback, questions, anything that doesn't fit a category below.
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com"
          class="mt-3 inline-block rounded-md bg-orange-500 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-orange-600"
        >
          hello@wrenchstack.com →
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">Corrections to product data</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
          If you spot wrong pricing, an outdated feature claim, or any factual error about a tool —
          email us with the specific page URL and what's wrong. We fix within 48 hours of confirmation
          and add a dated correction note. Vendor reps welcome (we won't gatekeep accuracy).
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com?subject=Correction%3A%20%5BTool%20name%5D"
          class="mt-3 inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-orange-600 hover:underline"
        >
          hello@wrenchstack.com (subject: "Correction: [tool]") →
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">Vendor / affiliate partnerships</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
          If you're an affiliate program manager wanting to partner, include in your first email:
          program name, commission structure, payout terms, and tracking platform (PartnerStack,
          Impact, direct, etc.). We respond fastest when these are clear upfront.
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:partners@wrenchstack.com?subject=Affiliate%20program%20inquiry%20%E2%80%94%20%5BCompany%5D"
          class="mt-3 inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-orange-600 hover:underline"
        >
          partners@wrenchstack.com →
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">Press / media</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Quote requests, expert commentary on trades software trends, or coverage inquiries.
          Available for interviews about the field service software market.
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:press@wrenchstack.com?subject=Press%20inquiry"
          class="mt-3 inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-orange-600 hover:underline"
        >
          press@wrenchstack.com →
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">Connect on LinkedIn</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">
          For warm intros, ongoing conversations, or just to follow the project's evolution.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bilal-homsi-11a4a340"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="mt-3 inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-orange-600 hover:underline"
        >
          Bilal Elhomsi on LinkedIn →
        </a>
      </div>

    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h2>What we DON'T respond to</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cold pitches to add your unrelated SaaS to our directory</strong> — we exclusively
          cover field service / trades software. If your tool isn't built for HVAC, plumbing, electrical,
          roofing, contractors, landscaping, cleaning, pest control, locksmith, garage door, appliance
          repair, or handyman businesses, we won't add it. No exceptions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pay-for-placement offers</strong> — we don't sell rankings, "featured" badges, or
          sponsored content. See our <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a> for why.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Mass-personalized outreach</strong> — if your email shows it was sent to 50+ "founders
          like me," it goes to the bin. Real partnership emails specify what you actually want and what
          you can offer.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>SEO / backlink swap pitches</strong> — we're not interested in link exchanges, guest
          posts for backlinks, or any other SEO trades.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Response time</h2>
      <p>
        Targets: 48 hours for corrections (often faster), 5 business days for partnership/press
        inquiries. WrenchStack is a solo operation, so peak weeks may run longer — if a week passes
        without acknowledgement on a partnership inquiry, send a one-line follow-up.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
        WrenchStack is operated by <strong>Bilal Elhomsi</strong>. Based in Saudi Arabia, editorial
        focus on the North American field service software market.
        See <a href="/about/">About WrenchStack</a> for the full backstory.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
